How do you pass data from parent to child component without using @api?
Companies that asked this: TCS, Salesforce, Infosys, IBM, Accenture, Capgemini

Answer:
While @api is the standard way to pass data from parent to child, there are several alternative methods when @api isn't suitable or available:

Alternative Methods:

Lightning Message Service (LMS) - For cross-component communication

Platform Events - For real-time data sharing

Local Storage/Session Storage - For persistent data (not recommended in LWC context)

URL Parameters - For navigation-based data

Event-Driven Patterns â€“ Using Custom Events to Pull Data (like PubSub)
